summary: This document is an FBI 302 form summarizing a May 19, 2021 call with a former Palm Beach Police Department detective regarding the 2005 investigation of Jeffrey Epstein. The detective recounts his participation in the October 20, 2005 search of Epstein's house, including observations of evidence like a phone message book and photographs of young women.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: The individual whose house was searched on October 20, 2005, as part of the Palm Beach Police Department investigation.

events.title: PBPD Investigation of Epstein
events.description: The Palm Beach Police Department conducted an investigation into Jeffrey Epstein.

events.title: Search of Epstein's House
events.description: Law enforcement executed a search of Jeffrey Epstein's house. A phone message book was identified as key evidence, and the house contained many photographs of young women.

keyFacts: A former Palm Beach Police Department detective participated in the October 20, 2005 search of Jeffrey Epstein's house.
During the search, a phone message book was identified as a key piece of evidence, described as 'the type of evidence they were looking for.'
The detective recalls Epstein's house contained 'lots of photographs of young women.'
The detective states he did not write reports or take notes beyond one supplement regarding the search and was not part of any trash searches.
